{{confused|Prix de Rome}} [[File:Baldric of the American Academy in Rome.jpg|thumb|Baldric of the American Academy in Rome]] [[File:Americanacademyrome.jpg|thumb| American Academy in Rome where prizewinners stay]] The '''Rome Prize''' is awarded by the [[American Academy in Rome]], in [[Rome]], Italy. Approximately thirty scholars and artists are selected each year to receive a study [[fellow]]ship at the academy.{{r|ig}} Prizes have been awarded annually since 1921, with a hiatus during the War years, from 1942 to 1949.{{r|mart|page=13}}
